00:34:59.904 --> 00:35:01.320
JARED DIAMOND:
Very good question.

00:35:01.320 --> 00:35:02.670
Thank you for raising that.

00:35:02.670 --> 00:35:04.020
I did not talk about it.

00:35:04.020 --> 00:35:08.080
So what is the significance
of a 2% difference?

00:35:08.080 --> 00:35:16.560
A rule of thumb in birds and
mammals is that, for example,

00:35:16.560 --> 00:35:20.740
the most abundant forest
bird in North America

00:35:20.740 --> 00:35:22.960
is the Red-eyed Vireo.

00:35:22.960 --> 00:35:25.270
And there's another
abundant forest bird

00:35:25.270 --> 00:35:27.240
called the White-eyed Vireo.

00:35:27.240 --> 00:35:29.260
The Red-eyed Vireo and
the White-eyed Vireo,

00:35:29.260 --> 00:35:32.070
they're both Vireos that
clown around in the treetops.

00:35:32.070 --> 00:35:34.430
The genetic difference between
Red- and White-eyed Vireo

00:35:34.430 --> 00:35:35.940
is 2%.

00:35:35.940 --> 00:35:46.150
The rule of thumb then
is that 2% or even 1%,

00:35:46.150 --> 00:35:48.210
the difference between
the common chimpanzee

00:35:48.210 --> 00:35:50.830
and the bonobo, the
pygmy chimpanzee, in DNA

00:35:50.830 --> 00:35:52.970
is about 1.5%.

00:35:52.970 --> 00:35:57.950
So 2% is the difference
between well-marked species.

00:35:57.950 --> 00:36:00.390
But it's not a spectacularly
big difference.

00:36:00.390 --> 00:36:03.610
Again, to calibrate
it, the difference

00:36:03.610 --> 00:36:09.980
between humans and Neanderthals,
modern humans and Neanderthals

00:36:09.980 --> 00:36:12.460
is considerably less than 1%.

00:36:12.460 --> 00:36:15.020
And it's now clear that
humans and Neanderthals

00:36:15.020 --> 00:36:17.690
hybridized to a limited extent.

00:36:17.690 --> 00:36:20.850
Common chimps and pygmy
chimps, about 1.5%.

00:36:20.850 --> 00:36:23.490
Humans and both of
those chimps, 2%.

00:36:23.490 --> 00:36:26.150
Humans and gorillas about 2.5%.

00:36:26.150 --> 00:36:29.260
Humans and orangutans,
maybe 4% or 5%.

00:36:29.260 --> 00:36:32.590
Humans and old world
monkeys, maybe 9%.

00:36:32.590 --> 00:36:35.447
So does that then calibrate
these differences?

00:36:35.447 --> 00:36:36.280
AUDIENCE: Thank you.

